      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// Use a Code node to safely extract the transcript.\n// Raw JSON Set mode breaks when the transcript contains newlines or quotes.\nconst body = $input.item.json.body || $input.item.json;\nconst message = body.message || {};\nconst call = message.call || {};\nconst structuredData = message.analysis?.structuredData || {};\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    eventType: message.type || 'unknown',\n    callId: call.id || 'unknown',\n    callStatus: call.status || 'unknown',\n    customerPhone: call.customer?.number || '',\n    transcript: message.transcript || '',\n    patientName: structuredData.patientName || '',\n    patientPhone: structuredData.patientPhone || '',\n    requestedDateTime: structuredData.requestedDateTime || '',\n    reason: structuredData.reason || structuredData.appointmentReason || '',\n    timestamp: new Date().toISOString()\n  }\n}];"
      },
      "id": "normalize-payload",
      "name": "Normalize VAPI Payload",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        660,
        550
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Analyze this VAPI webhook event and decide how to process it.\n\n**Event Data:**\n- Event Type: {{ $json.eventType }}\n- Call ID: {{ $json.callId }}\n- Patient Name: {{ $json.patientName || 'Not provided' }}\n- Patient Phone: {{ $json.patientPhone || $json.customerPhone || 'Not provided' }}\n- Requested DateTime: {{ $json.requestedDateTime || 'Not provided' }}\n- Reason: {{ $json.reason || 'Not provided' }}\n- Customer Phone (caller ID): {{ $json.customerPhone }}\n- Timestamp: {{ $json.timestamp }}\n\n**Call Transcript:**\n{{ $json.transcript || 'No transcript available' }}\n\nIf any patient fields above show 'Not provided', extract the correct values from the transcript before returning your decision.",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "You are the BizElevate Appointment Concierge Agent. Analyze VAPI webhook events and return structured decisions.\n\n## Your Task\nAnalyze the event and return a JSON decision object.\n\n## Decision Rules\n\n### For eventType = \"end-of-call-report\"\nThis is a completed call. You must:\n1. Determine the action: \"process_appointment\"\n2. Extract patient data — first from the structured fields, then from the transcript if any field is missing or empty\n3. Classify urgency based on the reason:\n   - \"emergency\": chest pain, difficulty breathing, severe bleeding, stroke symptoms, loss of consciousness\n   - \"urgent\": fever, infection, moderate pain, worsening symptoms, same-day needs\n   - \"routine\": check-ups, follow-ups, vaccinations, preventive care, general appointments\n\n### For any other eventType\nReturn action: \"acknowledge_only\"\n\n## Data Extraction Priority\nFor each field, use the first available source:\n1. Structured field (patientName, patientPhone, etc.) if non-empty\n2. Extract from the transcript text\n3. Fall back to default value\n\n## Data Defaults (last resort only)\n- patientName → \"Unknown Patient\"\n- patientPhone → customerPhone value, or \"Unknown\"\n- requestedDateTime → \"To be confirmed\"\n- reason → \"General appointment\"\n\n## Response Format\nAlways return valid JSON with these exact fields:\n{\n  \"action\": \"process_appointment\" or \"acknowledge_only\",\n  \"eventType\": \"the event type\",\n  \"callId\": \"the call ID\",\n  \"patientName\": \"full name extracted from transcript or field\",\n  \"patientPhone\": \"phone number extracted from transcript or field\",\n  \"patientFirstName\": \"first name only, for SMS greeting\",\n  \"requestedDateTime\": \"preferred time extracted from transcript or field\",\n  \"reason\": \"reason for visit extracted from transcript or field\",\n  \"urgency\": \"routine\", \"urgent\", or \"emergency\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"the timestamp\",\n  \"message\": \"brief status message\"\n}"
        }
      },
